        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Daemonic curses slither and crawl through malevolent runes carved in four stone pillars. HP is per-pillar.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-skill-check=\"thievery\" data-pf2-label=\"Disable Thievery DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span> (trained) to scratch out a pillar's runes, <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Dispel Magic]{Dispel Magic}</em> (2nd level; counteract DC 18) to counteract a pillar's magic, or <span data-pf2-skill-check=\"athletics\" data-pf2-traits=\"action:force-open\" data-pf2-label=\"Disable Athletics DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Athletics (Force Open)</span> to push a pillar over. Disabling a pillar requires two actions. Disabling all four pillars or slaying Sezruth disables the trap</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": 3,
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Routine </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>(4 actions):</strong> The trap loses 1 action each turn for each disabled pillar. On its initiative, the trap uses each action to afflict a different non-evil creature in the room with thirst. The creature must attempt a <span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-traits=\"\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude save</span>.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Critical Success:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The creature is temporarily immune to additional negative effects from the foretold ruin hazard&rsquo;s reaction for 24 hours. The hazard has no awareness of this immunity and continues to target this creature.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Success:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The creature is unaffected.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Failure:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Fatigued]{Fatigued} until they drink water.<br />If the creature was already fatigued, they take [[/r 1d6 #nonlethal mental]] nonlethal mental damage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The creature is fatigued until they drink water and takes 1d6 nonlethal mental damage. If the creature was already fatigued, they instead take [[/r 2d6 #nonlethal mental]]&nbsp;damage.</span></p>"
        },
